Summary: Terminal display freezes when saturated with input data
Class: semi-bug
Absent-in: 0.57
Present-in: 0.58
Content-type: text/x-html-body

<p>
Apparently the PuTTY terminal's display behaviour has changed when
it's being saturated with input data. It used to update the terminal
every once in a while (although not IIRC on every single bit of data),
whereas now it can apparently freeze until the flow abates (but still
munches lots of CPU).
